{"mode":"llm","topic":"Stereotype threat in STEM","opinion":"Stereotype threat, also known as imposter phenomenon, refers to the fear of confirming one's own stereotypes, particularly when belonging to underrepresented groups in STEM fields. This psychological phenomenon can lead to decreased performance and participation from individuals who experience it, ultimately hindering diversity and inclusion in these crucial fields. It is essential to address this issue by promoting inclusive environments that foster a sense of belonging, providing support structures for underrepresented groups, and challenging the systemic barriers that perpetuate stereotype threat. By doing so, we can create an enabling environment where everyone can thrive in STEM fields without feeling threatened or marginalized based on their identity."
